 ' Creating a "Move Circle" (or Bouncing Ball) game in Visual Studio 2022 using Visual Basic (VB.NET) is a great way to learn about GDI+ graphics and game loops.Based on the code you’ve been working on, here is the complete, structured guide to building the game from scratch.1. Project SetupOpen Visual Studio 2022.Create a new project: Windows Forms App (.NET Framework) or Windows Forms App (Visual Basic).Open the Toolbox and add these controls to your Form:PictureBox (Name: MainPictureBox) - This is your game screen.Timer (Name: Timer1) - This drives the animation.Button (Name: RestartButton) - To reset the game.2. Create the Ball Class (Ball.vb)Right-click your project > Add > Class > Name it Ball.vb. This class handles the logic for a single ball.VB.NetPublic Class Ball
    Private Const radius As Integer = 25
    Private ReadOnly kanji As String
    Private ReadOnly fontName As String
    Private ReadOnly brushColor As Brush
    Private ReadOnly pictureBox As PictureBox
    Private ReadOnly canvas As Bitmap
    
    Private position As New Point(0, 0)
    Private direction As New Point(1, 1) ' 1 = Right/Down, -1 = Left/Up
    Public Property Pitch As Integer = 5 ' Speed

    Public Sub New(pb As PictureBox, cv As Bitmap, cl As Brush, st As String, fn As String)
        pictureBox = pb
        canvas = cv
        brushColor = cl
        kanji = st
        fontName = fn
    End Sub

    ' Draw the ball and the character inside it
    Public Sub Draw(g As Graphics)
        g.SmoothingMode = Drawing2D.SmoothingMode.AntiAlias
        ' Draw Circle
        g.FillEllipse(brushColor, position.X, position.Y, radius * 2, radius * 2)
        ' Draw Text
        Using f As New Font(fontName, radius - 5)
            g.DrawString(kanji, f, Brushes.Black, position.X + 5, position.Y + 5)
        End Using
    End Sub

    ' Update position and handle wall bounces
    Public Sub Move()
        ' Move the ball
        position.X += (Pitch * direction.X)
        position.Y += (Pitch * direction.Y)

        ' Wall Collision (Right and Left)
        If position.X >= pictureBox.Width - (radius * 2) OrElse position.X <= 0 Then
            direction.X *= -1
        End If

        ' Wall Collision (Bottom and Top)
        If position.Y >= pictureBox.Height - (radius * 2) OrElse position.Y <= 0 Then
            direction.Y *= -1
        End If
    End Sub

    ' Randomize position (used during start/restart)
    Public Sub SetRandomPosition(rnd As Random)
        position.X = rnd.Next(0, pictureBox.Width - (radius * 2))
        position.Y = rnd.Next(0, pictureBox.Height - (radius * 2))
    End Sub
End Class
 ' 3. The Main Form Code (Form1.vb)This manages the canvas and the list of balls.VB.NetPublic Class Form1
    Private canvas As Bitmap
    Private balls As New List(Of Ball)
    Private ReadOnly rnd As New Random()

    Private Sub Form1_Load(sender As Object, e As EventArgs) Handles MyBase.Load
        InitializeGame()
        Timer1.Interval = 20 ' 50 Frames per second
        Timer1.Start()
    End Sub

    Private Sub InitializeGame()
        ' 1. Create the drawing surface
        canvas = New Bitmap(MainPictureBox.Width, MainPictureBox.Height)
        MainPictureBox.Image = canvas
        balls.Clear()

        ' 2. Create 5 balls with different colors
        Dim colors As Brush() = {Brushes.LightPink, Brushes.LightBlue, Brushes.LightGreen, Brushes.Gold, Brushes.Orange}
        Dim labels As String() = {"獲", "僕", "僕", "僕", "僕"}

        For i As Integer = 0 To 4
            Dim b As New Ball(MainPictureBox, canvas, colors(i), labels(i), Me.Font.Name)
            b.SetRandomPosition(rnd)
            balls.Add(b)
        Next
    End Sub

    ' The Game Loop
    Private Sub Timer1_Tick(sender As Object, e As EventArgs) Handles Timer1.Tick
        ' Create a fresh graphics object to clear the screen each frame
        Using g As Graphics = Graphics.FromImage(canvas)
            g.Clear(Color.White) ' Erase previous frame

            For Each b In balls
                b.Move()
                b.Draw(g)
            Next
        End Using

        ' Refresh the PictureBox to show the new drawing
        MainPictureBox.Invalidate()
    End Sub

    Private Sub RestartButton_Click(sender As Object, e As EventArgs) Handles RestartButton.Click
        InitializeGame()
    End Sub
End Class


 ' 4. Critical Concepts ExplainedThe Coordinate SystemWindows Forms uses a 2D coordinate system where the origin $(0, 0)$ is the top-left.X-axis: Increases to the right.Y-axis: Increases downward.The Game Loop (Timer)In a game, we don't just draw once. We perform these steps repeatedly (usually 30–60 times per second):Clear: Wipe the previous image.Update: Calculate new positions for all objects.Draw: Render the objects at their new positions.Refresh: Tell the computer to display the new image.Collision LogicTo make the ball bounce, we check if the ball's position has exceeded the width or height of the PictureBox. If it has, we multiply the direction by $-1$ to reverse it (e.g., changing $1$ to $-1$ makes it move left instead of right).Troubleshooting VS 2022Smoothness: If the ball flickers, ensure your PictureBox has DoubleBuffered set to True (you may need to create a custom PictureBox class to enable this property).Errors: If you see "Handles clause requires a WithEvents variable," make sure the name in your code matches the (Name) property of the button in the Designer.
पाईंले बनाउन खोज्नुभएको यो "Move Circle" (Bouncing Ball) गेम प्रोग्रामिङ सिक्नको लागि एकदमै राम्रो प्रोजेक्ट हो। भिजुअल स्टुडियो २०२२ (Visual Studio 2022) मा VB.NET प्रयोग गरेर यो गेम बनाउने प्रक्रियालाई म नेपालीमा व्याख्या गरिदिन्छु:

१. प्रोजेक्ट सेटअप (Project Setup)
Visual Studio 2022 खोल्नुहोस्।

Windows Forms App (Visual Basic) प्रोजेक्ट छान्नुहोस्।

तपाईंको फर्म (Form) मा यी तीन चिजहरू राख्नुहोस्:

PictureBox: यसको नाम MainPictureBox राख्नुहोस् (यसमा बलहरू गुड्छन्)।

Timer: यसको नाम Timer1 राख्नुहोस् (यसले एनिमेसन चलाउँछ)।

Button: यसको नाम RestartButton राख्नुहोस्।

२. बल क्लास (Ball Class) बुझौं
तपाईंले बनाउनुभएको Ball.vb क्लासले एउटा बलको सबै काम सम्हाल्छ।

Variables: यसमा बलको साइज (Radius), रङ (BrushColor), र कुन अक्षर (Kanji) देखाउने भन्ने जानकारी हुन्छ।

Move Method: यसले बललाई अगाडि बढाउँछ। यदि बलले भित्ता छोयो भने, यो फर्किन्छ (Bounce हुन्छ)।

दायाँ वा बायाँ भित्ता छोएमा: direction.X लाई उल्टो बनाउँछ।

माथि वा तलको भित्ता छोएमा: direction.Y लाई उल्टो बनाउँछ।

३. मुख्य अवधारणा (Core Concepts)
क. कोअर्डिनेट सिस्टम (Coordinate System)
कम्प्युटर स्क्रिनमा (0,0) बिन्दु माथिको बायाँ कुना (Top-Left) मा हुन्छ।

X बढ्नु भनेको दायाँ जानु हो।

Y बढ्नु भनेको तल जानु हो।

ख. गेम लुप (Game Loop)
हाम्रो Timer1_Tick ले गेम लुपको काम गर्छ। यसले हरेक सेकेन्डमा धेरै पटक यी कामहरू गर्छ:

Clear: पुरानो चित्र मेट्छ (g.Clear(Color.White))।

Move: बललाई नयाँ ठाउँमा सार्छ।

Draw: नयाँ ठाउँमा बल कोर्छ।

Refresh: स्क्रिनमा नयाँ चित्र देखाउँछ।

४. केही महत्त्वपूर्ण सुझावहरू
Flickering (झिम्काउने समस्या): यदि बल चल्दा स्क्रिन झिम्कियो भने PictureBox को DoubleBuffered प्रोपर्टी मिलाउनुपर्छ।

Collision Logic: बलको बाउन्ड्री चेक गर्दा जहिले पनि Radius (अर्धव्यास) लाई ध्यान दिनुपर्छ ताकि बल आधा भित्ताभित्र नछिरोस्।

तपाईंले दिएको कोड एकदम सही छ। यसलाई रन गर्दा ५ वटा फरक रङका बलहरू स्क्रिनमा उफ्रिन थाल्नेछन्। ती मध्ये एउटामा "獲" अक्षर हुनेछ भने बाँकीमा "僕" हुनेछ।

